 Robotic Media Definition

Robotic Media is a new infrastructure category defined in 2025 by Lorenzo Macali, Founder & CEO of Titano.

Robotic Media describes an infrastructure that transforms autonomous robots into programmable media nodes operating in the physical world.

Within this paradigm, autonomous machines act as nodes of a distributed media network capable of delivering content, collecting interactions and generating measurable data in real environments.

Titano & Titano OS is the proprietary infrastructure designed to enable Robotic Media networks.
